Great question! Decorators in Python can be implemented in a class method by using the `@` symbol to define a decorator function, which is then applied to the class method. Here's an example:
```
class MyClass:
    def my_method(self):
        # Method implementation
        pass

    @my_decorator
    def my_method(self):
        # Decorated method implementation
        pass
```
